## Recommendation Summary

### Intent Assessment
Documents the deterministic PII/API key/PHI detection system using 40+ regex patterns, automatically forcing private visibility on findings.

### Categorization Changes
- **ZETT**: "none (status: qualifying)" → "content_stage: reference" (Technical documentation about a security component. Reference stage. Missing content_stage field.)
- **TREE**: "technology/security, meta/workflows" → "meta/beestgraph/architecture, technology/security/appsec" (Primarily beestgraph architecture. Specifically application security.)
- **GRAPH**: "Likely has Document node" → "Ensure edges to Privacy Barriers, Qualification Pipeline, LLM Content Boundaries. PII Detection and Content Security Scanning should be Concept nodes." (Security component needs connections to privacy framework.)

### Metadata Issues
